        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks for <hi rend="italic">Forms of flowers</hi>.</p>  
<p>In his <hi rend="italic">Monographiae phanerogamarum</hi> [vol. 1 (1878)] he discusses transitional forms of dioecism in three genera of <hi rend="italic">Smilax</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Criticises CD’s use of the words "purpose" and "end", but acknowledges that in English they can mean both cause and effect.</p>
        </abstract>
